tourBios.curYrHigh: Made the cut in 6 of 7 starts during the first half of the PGA TOUR Latinoamérica season, with a solo 11th finish at the Honduras Open as his best in May.
tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T140 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament...In his first year on the Web.com Tour, played in 14 tournaments, making just three cuts. Best finish was a T31 at the Stonebrae Classic in August...Made one PGA TOUR Canada start, which resulted in a missed cut at the PC Financial Open in June. 

2013: Made the cut in five of nine PGA TOUR Canada starts. Best week was a T8 at the Times Colonist Island Savings Open...Was co-medalist (with James Sacheck) at his Second Stage Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament qualifier at McKinney, Texas.

OTHER DETAILS: Has competed on mini-tours, including the eGolf Professional Tour and the Gateway Tour.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played at Texas Tech University, where he won three letters for the Red Raiders and was a member of two teams that participated in the NCAAs…Also named to the Academic All-Big 12 team in 2011.
tourBios.personal: Says if he didn't play golf professionally, he'd either be a pro skydiver or an accountant…Biggest thrill outside golf was meeting President George W. Bush…Favorite course he's played is St. Andrews. Would like to play Cypress Point…Says his entrance song on the first tee would be "Who Let the Dogs out?"…Big fan of the San Diego Chargers and San Diego Padres, as well as the Texas Tech Red Raiders. Favorite athlete is the Chargers' safety Eric Weddle…Never travels without sunscreen and carries protein bars and nuts in his golf bag for snacks. Enjoys drinking Arizona green tea…Likes steak and eggs along with an In-N-Out Burger…Favorite app is Spotify…Enjoys watching "Family Guy" and the movie "Tin Cup."…Banff, Alberta, Canada is a favorite spot to visit…Would include Jennifer Aniston, his brother and his good friend Tyler in his dream foursome…Is involved with cancer research after losing an aunt and an uncle to cancer and also involved with Greenpeace…Has one younger brother…Played at Cathedral Catholic High School…Favorite golf memory was winning the Phil Mickelson San Diego Junior Championship.
